Control Groups (cgroups) for Resource Limits:

Cgroups are Linux kernel feature that limit, control and monitor resource usage of processes








                                                DAY -5 ------------------>
they ensure that:
1. No container can monopolize system resources
2. Fair sharing of CPU, memory and I/O

Without cgroups:
1. One container could consume all CPU or Ram
2. Host and other containers could crash

Types of resources Controlled by Cgroups:

1. CPU
	a. Limit CPU usage 
	b. Assign CPU shares
2. Memory
	a. Set maximum memory usage
	b. Kill contact if limit exceeded
3. Disk I/O

