Purpose of Namespaces: Process isolation (container is run alone even sharing the same OS kernel... This isolation is achieved by Linux namespaces)

Namespace is used for tagging predefined functions like -p, -e, etc which already exists in these namespaces

Real World Analogy: 
1. Container Image: Packed Lunch Box
2. Container Runtime: Person who opens it, serves food and cleans up

* Namespaces are Linux kernel features 

@ Namespace Used in Containers:
1. PID Namespace (Process Isolation)
    a. Each container has its own process tree
    b. Process IDS inside container start from 1
    c. A container cannot see host or other container processes
2. Network Namespaces :
    Each container gets:
        Its own IP address
        Its own ports
    Containers can run apps on the same port without conflict
3. Mount Namespace :
    Each container has itsown filesystem view
    File change inside container do not affect host 
4. UTS Namespace :
    Allows each Container to have its own hostname
5. User namespace:
    Maps container users to non-root users on host
    Improves security






